<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Small-size archisargid flies (body excluding antenna and genitalia less than 5 mm long); antennal scape long; arista (or stylus) absent; fork of R4+5 shallow, distad of level of R2+3 end; R5 ending before wing tip; discal cell short and wide (nearly 2.3 times as long as wide).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
From Chinese 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“changbing”">&quot;changbing&quot;</normalizedToken>
(long scape), and sargus referring to the Recent genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Sargus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sargus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sargus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Jurassic, China.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
The subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, 2012" authorityName="Zhang" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Archisargidae" genus="Flagellisargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Flagellisargus (Flagellisargus)" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Flagellisargus">Flagellisargus (Flagellisargus)</taxonomicName>
stat. n. includes three known species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, 2012" authorityName="Zhang" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Archisargidae" genus="Flagellisargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Flagellisargus (Flagellisargus) robustus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustus" subGenus="Flagellisargus">Flagellisargus (Flagellisargus) robustus</taxonomicName>
J Zhang, 2012a, 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, 2012" authorityName="Zhang" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Archisargidae" genus="Flagellisargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Flagellisargus (Flagellisargus) sinicus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinicus" subGenus="Flagellisargus">Flagellisargus (Flagellisargus) sinicus</taxonomicName>
J Zhang, 2012a and 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, 2012" authorityName="Zhang" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Archisargidae" genus="Flagellisargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Flagellisargus (Flagellisargus) venustus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venustus" subGenus="Flagellisargus">Flagellisargus (Flagellisargus) venustus</taxonomicName>
J Zhang, 2012a. Among them, the first and the third species are erected based on nearly complete male flies, the second one with head and abdomen missing. This known subgenus differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, 2012" authorityName="Zhang" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Archisargidae" genus="Flagellisargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Flagellisargus (Changbingisargus)" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Changbingisargus">Flagellisargus (Changbingisargus)</taxonomicName>
subgen. n. in the following aspects: moderate-size archisargid flies (body excluding antenna and genitalia more than 9 mm long); antennal scape short; arista (or stylus) present; fork of R4+5 relatively deep, just at level of R2+3 end; R5 ending just at wing tip; discal cell narrow and long (nearly three times or more as long as wide).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
Although the head and abdomen are missing, 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, 2012" authorityName="Zhang" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Archisargidae" genus="Flagellisargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Flagellisargus (Flagellisargus) venustus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venustus" subGenus="Flagellisargus">Flagellisargus (Flagellisargus) venustus</taxonomicName>
demonstrates close similarities in wing venation to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, 2012" authorityName="Zhang" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Archisargidae" genus="Flagellisargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Flagellisargus (Flagellisargus) sinicus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinicus" subGenus="Flagellisargus">Flagellisargus (Flagellisargus) sinicus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, 2012" authorityName="Zhang" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Archisargidae" genus="Flagellisargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Flagellisargus (Flagellisargus) robustus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustus" subGenus="Flagellisargus">Flagellisargus (Flagellisargus) robustus</taxonomicName>
: fork of R4+5 relatively deep, just at level of R2+3 end; R5 ending at wing tip; discal cell narrow and long, nearly 3.5 times as long as wide (Fig. 3
<normalizedToken originalValue="A–C">A-C</normalizedToken>
). Thus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, 2012" authorityName="Zhang" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Archisargidae" genus="Flagellisargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Flagellisargus (Flagellisargus) venustus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venustus" subGenus="Flagellisargus">Flagellisargus (Flagellisargus) venustus</taxonomicName>
should be retained in 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, 2012" authorityName="Zhang" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Archisargidae" genus="Flagellisargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Flagellisargus (Flagellisargus)" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Flagellisargus">Flagellisargus (Flagellisargus)</taxonomicName>
rather than be assigned to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, 2012" authorityName="Zhang" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Archisargidae" genus="Flagellisargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Flagellisargus (Changbingisargus)" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Changbingisargus">Flagellisargus (Changbingisargus)</taxonomicName>
subgen. n.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
